---
import CaseStudyLayout from '../../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro';
---

<CaseStudyLayout
    title="Hill's Browse by Condition | Jared Smith"
    projectTitle="Hill's Browse by Condition"
    type="UI/UX Design"
    tagline="Helping veterinary professionals find the right nutrition for their pet's specific health condition — without getting lost in a 200+ product catalog."
    client="Hill's Pet Nutrition"
    role="Lead UI Designer"
    timeline="14 weeks"
    platform="Web"
    coverImage="/assets/hillsvet/hillsvet_cover.jpg"
    nextHref="/work/kc-zoo"
    nextTitle="Kansas City Zoo Map"
>
    <div class="case-study-section">
        <span class="case-study-section__label">Overview</span>
        <h2 class="case-study-section__title">Title needed</h2>
        <div class="case-study-section__body">
            <p>Hill's Pet Nutrition operates two parallel web presences: hillspet.com for consumers, and hillsvet.com for veterinary professionals. The vet-facing site is a clinical tool — vets use it to look up therapeutic nutrition options for their patients, compare products, and build feeding plans.</p>
            <p>The "Browse by Condition" page is one of hillsvet.com's most-used features. It lets veterinary professionals find the right Hill's product based on a patient's primary condition and any concurrent secondary conditions — navigating across both the Prescription Diet and Science Diet product lines. The page needed a full redesign to address usability problems, introduce new features requested by the client, and bring the interface up to modern accessibility standards.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

